Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "povreda":

1. *Povreda* je zahtevala hitnu medicinsku intervenciju. (Injury* required urgent medical intervention.)
2. Nakon nesreće, osetila je jaku *povredu* u leđima. (After the accident, she felt a strong *injury* in her back.)
3. Policija je istraživala uzrok saobraćajne *povrede*. (The police investigated the cause of the traffic *injury*.)
4. Sportisti se često suočavaju sa *povredama* tokom treninga. (Athletes often face *injuries* during training.)
5. Lekar je pregledao pacijenta i utvrdio da ima tešku *povredu*. (The doctor examined the patient and determined that he had a serious *injury*.)
6. Sudija je pokazao žuti karton igraču zbog faula i *povrede* protivnika. (The referee showed a yellow card to the player for a foul and *injury* to the opponent.)
7. Kompanija je izbegla veliku *povredu* zaposlenih zahvaljujući brzoj evakuaciji. (The company avoided a major *injury* to its employees thanks to a quick evacuation.)
8. Nije bilo vidljivih *povreda* na telu žrtve, ali je kasnije utvrđeno da je pretrpela teške unutrašnje povrede. (There were no visible *injuries* on the victim's body, but it was later determined that she had suffered serious internal injuries.)

I hope these examples help!